<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="B" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Baggage" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Baggage,</orth> 1) the necessaries of an army, only in the phrase <cit><quote>"with bag and b.":</quote> <bibl n="shak. ayl 3.2.170" default="NO" valid="yes">As III, 2, 170</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. wt 1.2.206" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. I, 2, 206</bibl>.<lb />2) term of contempt for a worthless woman: <cit><quote>you witch, you hag, you b.</quote> <bibl n="shak. wiv 4.2.194" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. IV, 2, 194</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. err 3.1.57" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. III, 1, 57</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. err 3.1.3" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. Ind. 1, 3.</bibl> <bibl n="shak. rom 3.5.157" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. III, 5, 157</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 3.5.157" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. III, 5, 157</bibl> <bibl n="shak. per 4.2.24" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. IV, 2, 24</bibl>. IV. <bibl n="shak. per 4.6.20" default="NO" valid="yes">6, 20</bibl>.
